Kay,
 
We need to incorporate the following components into the Genuity Solutions Inc. Master Agreement:

We need a parent guarantee from Genuity Inc. ($10MM) and are willing to reciprocate (Enron Corp. $10MM).  We need to insert Events of Default with respect to guarantor. (Credit Support Annex section 4 and 5 from our MSA) 
We need to insert netting (MSA section 6.4) and close-out setoff (MSA section 5.7). 
We need to insert the ability to request financial statements from the Guarantor if they are not publicly available (MSA section 8). 
The assignment language needs to be re-amended.  Both parties can only assign to an affiliate that is at least as creditworthy as the existing - i.e. we need to maintain the parent guarantee. (MSA section 10.4). The current amendment is unclear whether or not Genuity is the only party allowed to assign to an affiliate. 
We need a bilateral bankruptcy event of default. (MSA section 5.1(iv)). 
There is no clause regarding disputes of invoices.  We can use our standard language from the MSA.(Section 6.3). 
Do we need to state that we are a forward contract merchant?

Please let me know if you have any questions.
 
Thanks,
 
Jane Wilhite
ext. 35063

